Interface ParameterSpace<P>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLSTMLayerSpace, AbstractParameterSpace, ActivationLayerSpace, ActivationParameterSpaceAdapter, AdaGradSpace, AdaMaxSpace, AdamSpace, AlphaDropoutSpace, AutoEncoderLayerSpace, BaseConvolutionLayerSpace, BaseLayerSpace, BaseNetworkSpace, BaseOutputLayerSpace, BasePretrainNetworkLayerSpace, BaseUpdaterSpace, BatchNormalizationSpace, Bidirectional, BooleanSpace, CenterLossOutputLayerSpace, ComputationGraphSpace, ContinuousParameterSpace, ConvolutionLayerSpace, Deconvolution2DLayerSpace, DenseLayerSpace, DiscreteParameterSpace, DropoutLayerSpace, DropoutSpace, DropoutSpace, EmbeddingLayerSpace, ExponentialScheduleSpace, FeedForwardLayerSpace, FixedLayerSpace, FixedValue, GaussianDropoutSpace, GaussianNoiseSpace, GlobalPoolingLayerSpace, GravesBidirectionalLSTMLayerSpace, GravesLSTMLayerSpace, IntegerParameterSpace, InverseScheduleSpace, LayerSpace, LocalResponseNormalizationLayerSpace, LossFunctionParameterSpaceAdapter, LossLayerSpace, LSTMLayerSpace, MathOp, MultiLayerSpace, NadamSpace, NesterovsSpace, OCNNLayerSpace, OutputLayerSpace, PairMathOp, ParameterSpaceAdapter, PolyScheduleSpace, RmsPropSpace, RnnOutputLayerSpace, SeparableConvolution2DLayerSpace, SgdSpace, SigmoidScheduleSpace, StepScheduleSpace, SubsamplingLayerSpace, VariationalAutoencoderLayerSpace

    public interface ParameterSpace<P>
    ParameterSpace: defines the acceptable ranges of values a given parameter may take. Note that parameter spaces can be simple (like ParameterSpace<Double>) or complicated, including multiple nested ParameterSpaces

    • Method Detail

      • getValue

        P getValue(double[] parameterValues)
        Generate a candidate given a set of values. These values are then mapped to a specific candidate, using some mapping function (such as the prior probability distribution)
        Parameters:
        parameterValues - A set of values, each in the range [0,1], of length numParameters()

      • numParameters

        int numParameters()
        Get the total number of parameters (hyperparameters) to be optimized. This includes optional parameters from different parameter subpaces. (Thus, not every parameter may be used in every candidate)
        Returns:
        Number of hyperparameters to be optimized

      • collectLeaves

        java.util.List<ParameterSpace> collectLeaves()
        Collect a list of parameters, recursively. Note that leaf parameters are parameters that do not have any nested parameter spaces

      • getNestedSpaces

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,ParameterSpace> getNestedSpaces()
        Get a list of nested parameter spaces by name. Note that the returned parameter spaces may in turn have further nested parameter spaces. The map should be empty for leaf parameter spaces
        Returns:
        A map of nested parameter spaces

      • isLeaf

        boolean isLeaf()
        Is this ParameterSpace a leaf? (i.e., does it contain other ParameterSpaces internally?)

      • setIndices

        void setIndices(int... indices)
        For leaf ParameterSpaces: set the indices of the leaf ParameterSpace. Expects input of length numParameters(). Throws exception if isLeaf() is false.
        Parameters:
        indices - Indices to set. Length should equal numParameters()
